The paper deals with the problem of finding certain problematic structures in LDPC codes, which are commonly studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and coding theory (cs.CC) communities. The paper also involves proving NP-hardness results, which is a common topic in theoretical computer science (cs.DM). The structures being studied, namely leafless elementary trapping sets and elementary absorbing sets, are combinatorial objects, which are also studied in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). Finally, the paper involves analyzing the performance of iterative decoding algorithms, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
